quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Merciful
  55,2,taught the Qur'an
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,taught him plain speech
  55,5,The sun and the moon have their appointed time
  55,6,The herbs and the trees adore
  55,7,"And the heavens, He raised them and set the balance"
  55,8,that ye should not be outrageous in the balance
  55,9,"But weigh ye aright, and stint not the balance"
  55,10,And the earth He has set it for living creatures
  55,11,"therein are fruits and palms, with sheaths"
  55,12,and grain with chaff and frequent shoots
  55,13,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,14,He created men of crackling clay like the potters
  55,15,And He created the ginn from smokeless fire
  55,16,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,17,The Lord of the two easts and the Lord of the two wests
  55,18,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,19,He has let loose the two seas that meet together
  55,20,between them is a barrier they cannot pass
  55,21,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,22,He brings forth from each pearls both large and small
  55,23,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,24,His are the ships which rear aloft in the sea like mountains
  55,25,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny